236
00:12:59,816 --> 00:13:01,397
and loop and loop, like on Tinder,

237
00:13:01,437 --> 00:13:03,618
you can loop and loop as long as you want.

238
00:13:03,978 --> 00:13:07,660
So to do that, I created a system

239
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:10,241
that I call Probabilistic Driven Narrative

240
00:13:10,281 --> 00:13:12,262
because it's a bit pedantic and I like it.

241
00:13:13,823 --> 00:13:16,304
So I couldn't do branching path narrative,

242
00:13:16,384 --> 00:13:18,005
especially as I am to be lazy.

243
00:13:18,365 --> 00:13:22,267
It's just crazy, you have four draws here,

244
00:13:22,567 --> 00:13:23,007
imagine.

245
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:27,543
or I would deal with hundreds of cards, it's not possible.

246
00:13:27,963 --> 00:13:29,345
And it creates a lot of garbage.

247
00:13:29,405 --> 00:13:33,028
So instead I created this probabilistic driven narrative.

248
00:13:35,330 --> 00:13:40,835
It's a relatively simple idea based on basic probability.

249
00:13:41,896 --> 00:13:45,060
and that are actually very useful tools

250
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:48,283
that I will try to explain here.

251
00:13:48,343 --> 00:13:52,287
So basically, I check the state of the kingdom,

252
00:13:52,588 --> 00:13:56,372
which is made of different variables that I collect, okay?

253
00:13:57,273 --> 00:14:00,656
And against that state, I select all the cards

254
00:14:00,776 --> 00:14:01,818
that fit in that state.

255
00:14:03,319 --> 00:14:06,321
And I put them in this bag, like a bag of cards if you want,

256
00:14:06,641 --> 00:14:09,343
that adapts to the number of cards that are in the bag.

257
00:14:09,703 --> 00:14:12,184
